{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dca27c77-ca65-481e-932d-195d3b08ce25","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n**1. Project file — `MyTests.csproj`**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.3\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it — `MSTest.Sdk` bundles the test framework, runner, and analyzers automatically.\n\n**2. Enable parallel execution — add a single file like `AssemblyInfo.cs`:**\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting;\n\n[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]\n```\n\nThis runs test **classes** in parallel (use `ExecutionScope.MethodLevel` to parallelize individual methods too).\n\n**3. Opt out for database tests — use `[DoNotParallelize]`:**\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Insert_Record() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Can_Read_After_Write() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\nAll classes marked `[DoNotParallelize]` run sequentially **after** all parallelizable tests finish.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `MSTest.Sdk` replaces `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` — no manual `PackageReference` needed\n- `Parallelize` at assembly level is the global switch\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` can go on a class or individual method\n- Sequential tests always run last to avoid contention with parallel ones","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7dd2253a-8408-4c79-a2a3-f3f774ab339d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a general question about MSTest setup. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk, parallel execution, and the `[DoNotParallelize]` attribute.\n\nHere's the recommended setup:\n\n1. **Simplest project file with MSTest.Sdk**: Use `<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.x.x\">` which eliminates the need for explicit package references.\n\n2. **Parallel by default**: MSTest supports parallelization via assembly-level attributes or `.runsettings`.\n\n3. **Sequential database tests**: Use `[DoNotParallelize]` on test classes that need sequential execution.\n\n\nNow I'll walk through a concrete example showing how to set this up.","outputTokens":585,"requestId":"BD04:2586A7:1F03A8C:230CE6E:6A07CF32"},"id":"6fd4aabd-f92d-4484-b232-28bd9c2d3eb5","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:58:22.936Z","parentId":"35415a2b-4033-418b-ba11-13063d052f5a"}
